    "body": "### Problem\n\n## Description\n\nThe hover window style for the lspconfig is not as expected\n\n## Behavior\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/397905d9-ca85-44ed-b460-6651bbdc3312)\n\n## Config\n\nmini_init.lua\n\n```lua\n-- Set up LazyVim if it's not installed\nlocal lazypath = vim.fn.stdpath(\"data\") .. \"/lazy/lazy.nvim\"\nif not vim.loop.fs_stat(lazypath) then\n  vim.fn.system({\n    \"git\", \"clone\", \"--filter=blob:none\",\n    \"https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim.git\",\n    \"--branch=stable\", lazypath\n  })\nend\nvim.opt.rtp:prepend(lazypath)\n\n-- Lazy.nvim plugin setup\nrequire(\"lazy\").setup({\n  -- LSP configuration\n  {\n    \"neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",\n    config = function()\n      local lspconfig = require(\"lspconfig\")\n\n      -- Example LSP server (replace with your desired server)\n      lspconfig.lua_ls.setup({\n        on_attach = function(client, bufnr)\n          -- Set key mapping for hover\n          vim.api.nvim_buf_set_keymap(bufnr, 'n', 'K', '<cmd>lua vim.lsp.buf.hover()<CR>', { noremap = true, silent = true })\n        end\n      })\n    end\n  },\n\n  -- Optional: Treesitter for better syntax highlighting\n  {\n    \"nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\",\n    build = \":TSUpdate\",\n    config = function()\n      require(\"nvim-treesitter.configs\").setup({\n        ensure_installed = { \"lua\", \"python\", \"javascript\", \"typescript\" },\n        highlight = { enable = true },\n      })\n    end\n  },\n\n  -- Optional: Completion (nvim-cmp)\n  {\n    \"hrsh7th/nvim-cmp\",\n    dependencies = { \"hrsh7th/cmp-nvim-lsp\" },\n    config = function()\n      local cmp = require(\"cmp\")\n      cmp.setup({\n        mapping = cmp.mapping.preset.insert({\n          [\"<Tab>\"] = cmp.mapping.select_next_item(),\n          [\"<S-Tab>\"] = cmp.mapping.select_prev_item(),\n          [\"<CR>\"] = cmp.mapping.confirm({ select = true }),\n        }),\n        sources = cmp.config.sources({\n          { name = \"nvim_lsp\" }\n        })\n      })\n    end\n  }\n})\n\n-- Basic settings\nvim.o.syntax = \"on\"\nvim.o.termguicolors = true\nvim.o.number = true\nvim.o.relativenumber = true\n\n-- Map the 'K' key to show the hover window\nvim.api.nvim_set_keymap('n', 'K', '<cmd>lua vim.lsp.buf.hover()<CR>', { noremap = true, silent = true })\n  -- Customize hover window style\nvim.lsp.handlers[\"textDocument/hover\"] = vim.lsp.with(vim.lsp.handlers.hover, {\n        border = \"rounded\", -- Options: \"single\", \"double\", \"rounded\", \"solid\"\n        max_width = 80,\n        max_height = 30,\n        winhighlight = \"Normal:Normal,FloatBorder:FloatBorder\", -- Highlight groups\n})\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean -u mini_init.lua mini_init.lua\n2. press `K` on any word to open the hover window\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n* I expect the style of the window border can be customized according to the configuration, such as rounded, single, double and solid.\n* In other configuration files, I can customize the border styles of diagnostic window and so on, but only hover window doesn't under expected.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot test on vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos 14.7.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm.app 3.5.11\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
